                                    <desc type="Record"/>
                                    <locus target="#1r"/>
                                    <q xml:lang="en">"History of our Fathers, the monks who sprang from Dabra Libānos: ʾAnorewos of Warab, Tadewos of Ṭǝlālǝš (sic) and Dabra Dǝḫuḫān, Gabra Krǝstos of Dǝmbiyā, Zenā Mārqos of Morat, Sāmuʾel of Dabra Wagal (sic), Yosef of ʾƎnnārʾǝt, Qawestos of M(aḥ)āggǝl, ʾAdḫānani (sic) of Dāmot, ʾIyosyās of Waǧ, Matyas of Faṭagār, another ʾAdḫānani (sic) of Dawāro, Madḫane ʾƎgziʾ of Tǝgrāy. All of them fulfill their office, each according to their own rank".</q>
                                    <p>The note records the names of prominent monks coming from the monastic community of <placeName corresp="LOC2297DabraL"/>:
                                        <persName corresp="PRS1955Anorewos"/>, <persName corresp="PRS9087Tadewos"/>, <persName corresp="PRS4279GabraKr"/>, <persName corresp="PRS10708ZenaMa"/>, <persName corresp="PRS8485Samuel"/>, <persName corresp="PRS10455Yosef"/> (?), <persName corresp="PRS8023Qawestos"/>, <persName corresp="PRS1417Adhani"/>, <persName corresp="PRS10778Iyosyas"/>, <persName corresp="PRS6913Matyas"/>, <persName corresp="PRS10779Adhani"/>, <persName corresp="PRS6445Madhanin"/>.
                                        The note displays resemblance with a passage of the <ptr target="LIT1445GadlaF"/> and of <ptr target="LIT3143Ledata"/>.</p>
                                    <bibl><ptr target="bm:Turaiev1908Aaron"/><citedRange unit="page">198 (text), 179 (tr.)</citedRange></bibl>
                                    <bibl><ptr target="bm:Getatchew1982Monast"/><citedRange unit="page">28-29</citedRange></bibl>
                                </item>
